Description: Fragment of shoulder of Aeolic pottery dinos; interior glazed; exterior slipped white; part of goat to right, with some filling ornament; graffito outside.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ3, probably (possibly)
Curator's comments: Possibly marked in pencil Φ3. This marking was read by Don Bailey during registration in 1965, but it is now very faint and cannot be verified.

The piece is from the same vase as 1924,1201.1028 (wheelmarks on both sides) and very probably 1924,1201.1036. It does not join 1028, despite the epigraphic suitability of the connection. This would confirm that it carried a dedication by two (or more) persons with 'anetheke' repeated. See comment on 1036. Boston MFA 88.949 may also belong.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.79)
